@Vital.Impacts is excited to launch a fundraising fine art print sale in support of Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e), Africa's first indigenous-owned elephant sanctuary, and I am thrilled to be a part of it!!!

Funds raised will send 13 orphaned elephants back to the wild.This moment is such an immense achievement for the sanctuary and their brave young orphans – who arrived with considerable odds stacked against them, and so much to overcome.

I am honored to support this important moment and highlight the vital link between empowering women, environmental stewardship, and wildlife preservation.

Learn more and explore all the exquisite works available by visiting bit.ly/vitalimpactssale (link in profile). @momatiukeastcott  @jimrichardsonng  @michaelnicknichols  @amytoensing  @melissafarlow

The Blue Paradox is an immersive experience about the ocean plastic crisis. @msichicago @randyolson @melissafarlow

Photo by @melissafarlow // @TheBlueParadox at Chicago’s Museum of Science and Industry is an very cool, immersive experience about the environment. The mission is to educate and inspire us all to do our part collectively and reduce plastic in our oceans that impacts the planet. It’s engaging and fun experience for all ages, yet you leave and think about the message.  The show features photos by @randyolson - and across the hall is a fabulous exhibit about shrinking glaciers by my friend James Balog - titled Extreme Ice. @randyolson @theblueparadox @msichicago @james_balog @thephotosociety

@melissafarlow // It was shocking to go from an inspiring exhibit at the Museum of Science and Industry called The Blue Paradox featuring photos by @randyolson and many others work addressing issues of plastic pollution and climate change … AND walk outside into Chicago bathed in brown smoke from wildfires making it the most polluted air in any city in the world. I never thought I’d live to see climate change.  @randyolson @theblueparadox @msichicago @thephotosociety
